modules.description: Provides positioning strategies for labels relative to anchor points, including directional placement (center, start, end, left, right, top, bottom) and custom angles in degrees. Operates on a type `t` that represents alignment configurations. Used to control text or element placement in graphical interfaces, such as positioning tooltips or markers in a visualization.

Provides methods to determine the central point, start, and end positions of an element, using a custom type `t` that wraps a DOM element. Operates on JavaScript objects representing HTML elements through the Js_of_ocaml library. Used to calculate positional relationships for layout adjustments or animations.

Controls the visibility of labels based on boolean input or automatic overlap detection. Operates on a custom type `t` representing visibility states. Used to dynamically show or hide labels in a graphical interface to prevent clutter.

Provides constants for text alignment settings, including left, center, and right alignment, with aliases for common directions. Works with the `t` type to represent alignment configurations. Used to control text positioning in UI elements or formatted output.

Provides functions to generate and configure horizontal bar charts, including data series, axis labels, and styling options. Works with OCaml lists and records representing chart data, scales, and options. Used to embed interactive charts in web applications with dynamic data visualization.
